---
title: Soba Noodle Stir-Fry with Corn, Mushrooms & Red Pepper
description: We're using soba noodles -  a traditionally Japanese ingredient - in a very non-traditional way here. We love the unexpected combo of hearty buckwheat noodles and a creamy, parmesan-spiked sauce. A quick satué of mushrooms, sweet corn, and red bell pepper adds bursts of texture throughout the dish.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54ecda5b6ced6e44738b456a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/54ecda5b6ced6e44738b456a.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/soba-noodle-stir-fry-54ecda5b6ced6e44738b456a
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 518 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 4 g
---

Bring a #large pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cut the
@corn{1} kernels off the cob. Thinly slice the @scallions{2} and @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Mince
or grate the @garlic{2%clove}. Core, seed, and remove white veins from @red bell pepper{1}, then thinly
slice.

> Runaway corn kernels? Lay a large sheet of parchment paper or foil over your cutting board to
> gather the loose kernels that you've sliced.

Place a #large bowl{} with ice water next to the stove. Add the @buckwheat soba noodles{1%bunch}
to the boiling water. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of
cooking water, then place the noodles in the ice water to stop the cooking. Set aside in the
ice water.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large non-stick pan{} over medium heat. Add the bell pepper
and mushroom and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes},
until softened. Add the garlic, scallions, and corn. Cook, tossing, about ~{2%minutes},
until mushrooms are very soft and bell peppers are crisp-tender.

Drain the soba noodles and add them to the pan along with the @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and
reserved pasta water. Toss to combine and cool for a minute or two until sauce has thickened
and soba noodles are warmed through. Toss with half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper.

Serve the soba noodles with a sprinkle of the remaining parmesan cheese on top.